#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:17
msgid "Read the Docs has the following search features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:19
msgid "Search across :doc:`subprojects </subprojects>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:20
msgid ""
"Subprojects allow you to host multiple discrete projects on a single domain. "
"Every subproject hosted on that same domain is included in the search "
"results of the main project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:23
msgid "Search results land on the exact content you were looking for"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:24
msgid ""
"We index every heading in the document, allowing you to get search results "
"exactly to the content that you are searching for. Try this out by searching "
"for `\"full-text search\"`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:28
msgid "Full control over which results should be listed first"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:29
msgid ""
"Set a custom rank per page, allowing you to deprecate content, and always "
"show relevant content to your users first. See :ref:`config-file/v2:search."
"ranking`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:33
msgid "Search across projects you have access to"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:34
msgid ""
"Search across all the projects you have access to in your Dashboard. **Don't "
"remember where you found that document the other day? No problem, you can "
"search across them all.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:38
msgid ""
"You can also specify what projects you want to search using the ``project:"
"{name}`` syntax, for example: `\"project:docs project:dev search\"`_. See :"
"doc:`/server-side-search/syntax`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:43
msgid "Special query syntax for more specific results"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:44
msgid ""
"We support a full range of search queries. You can see some examples at :ref:"
"`server-side-search/syntax:special queries`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:47
msgid "Configurable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:48
msgid ""
"Tweak search results according to your needs using a :ref:`configuration "
"file <config-file/v2:search>`. You can also enable or disable the search "
"modal, and toggle the subprojects filter shown inside it, from your "
"project's :guilabel:`Settings`, in the left bar, under :guilabel:`Search`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:54
msgid "Ready to use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:55
msgid ""
"We override the default search engine of your Sphinx project with ours to "
"provide you with all these benefits within your project. We fallback to the "
"built-in search engine from your project if ours doesn't return any results, "
"just in case we missed something |:smile:|."
msgstr ""

