#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:89
msgid "Configuring search"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:91
msgid ""
"You can configure search options for your project from the :term:`dashboard`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:93
msgid "Go to the :term:`dashboard`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:94
msgid "Click on a project name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:95
msgid "Go to :guilabel:`Settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:96
msgid "In the left bar, go to :guilabel:`Search`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:98
msgid ""
"From there you can toggle :guilabel:`Enable search modal`, which controls "
"whether the Read the Docs search modal is shown in your documentation, and :"
"guilabel:`Show subprojects filter in search modal`, which controls whether "
"readers can filter search results by :doc:`subproject </subprojects>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:104
msgid "How main content is detected"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:106
msgid ""
"Server Side Search indexes the \"main content\" of HTML pages, ignoring "
"headers, footers, navigation, and other page elements that aren't part of "
"the documentation content itself. This keeps results focused and avoids "
"repeated elements like nav menus from polluting relevance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../server-side-search/index.rst:110
msgid ""
"For details on how the main content area is detected, see :ref:`reference/"
"main-content-detection:detection logic`."
msgstr ""
